			<div class="slide">
			<img src="images/_report.png" alt="Wander CO Travel Report Preview">	
			<div class="slide-text">
				<h3>WanderCo Annual Report</h3>
				<a href="projects2/report.pdf" target="_blank">View Full Report</a>
				<p>The WanderCo Annual Report highlights my technical design abilities through a professional, structured visual approach. Designed for an organic, positive, and sustainability-driven travel brand, the layout balances clarity with a cohesive brand voice. Organizing extensive information—graphs, data points, and icon systems—challenged me to refine my skills in hierarchy, consistency, and visual communication. This project expanded my range as a designer, strengthening my ability to translate complex content into an engaging, accessible experience. </p>
			</div>	
			</div>

			<div class="slide">
			<img src="images/_paw2.png" alt="Paw Primal Package Design Preview">	
			<div class="slide-text">
				<h3>Paw Package Design</h3>
				<a href="projects2/paw.pdf" target="_blank">View Full Package Design</a>
				<p>Creating the Paw Primal and Paw Instinct package design involved developing the full branding and packaging system for a paleo diet pet food brand, from logo design to package layout and visual style. The goal was to create a cohesive identity that communicates the brand's focus on pet health and nutrition. I began with extensive research to understand the brand's values and positioning, exploring multiple design directions before settling on the final approach. This project allowed me to experiment with different visual styles while also considering hierarchy, clarity, and the effective presentation of information within packaging constraints. It was an engaging challenge that expanded my abilities in brand storytelling, visual communication, and design problem-solving. </p>
			</div>
			</div>

			<div class="slide">
			<img src="images/_calendar.png" alt="Calendar Spread Design">	
			<div class="slide-text">
				<h3>Calendar Spread Design</h3>
				<a href="projects2/caledar.pdf" target="_blank">View PDF</a>
				<p>This project involved designing a two-page calendar spread for September and October 2025 with a focus on visual cohesion, originality, and functionality. I explored ways to create a design that was aesthetically engaging without relying on clichés, while also considering practical uses for the end user—such as allowing buyers to cut out the artwork as decor after the year ends. The concept of stamps provided a versatile and consistent framework for the calendar, allowing for variation while maintaining a unified style. I selected marigolds for September, reflecting the month's symbolic flower, and a pie for October to evoke warmth and an inviting tone. The result is a clean, coherent design that balances consistency, functionality, and visual appeal.</p>
			</div>
			</div>

			<div class="slide">
